From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: robert-brunson-fragile <siinspam@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 14:20:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 18/19] feat(api): persist /v1/runs events durably alongside
 the SSE stream
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The upstream /v1/runs/{run_id}/events SSE stream is single-consumer and
ephemeral: the queue is popped on first detach and events emitted after
that are dropped. Keep the endpoint exactly as upstream ships it, and
additionally persist every run lifecycle event so any number of clients
can observe or replay runs through the durable session sync surface.

- POST /v1/runs registers the run in ResponseStore (create_session_run)
  and every event that feeds the per-run queue — message.delta, tool.*,
  reasoning.available, approval.request/responded,
  run.started/completed/failed/cancelled — is also persisted via a new
  _emit_run_event helper (put_session_run_event + subscriber notify) and
  observed via GET /api/sessions/{id}/subscribe. The 202 response now
  includes session_id so clients know what to subscribe to.
- Approval flow gains a polling path: approval.request is stashed as
  pending_approval in the run status (GET /v1/runs/{id} shows
  status=waiting_for_approval plus the redacted request) and cleared on
  response. _set_run_status now removes fields passed as None.
- Orphan sweep fix: only reap runs whose task is gone or done.
  Previously a long (>300s) run with no attached SSE consumer had its
  stop/approval bookkeeping dropped mid-flight by the TTL sweep.

Tests: durable lifecycle persistence, stop reaching a terminal durable
state, and approval status polling + durable replay added alongside the
existing SSE stream tests (all upstream tests kept).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

